post_text:
Dear Meyersdale Area School District Families,

The Meyersdale Area School District has submitted our Phased School Reopening Health and Safety Plan for the Fall of 2020. If our County remains in the Green Phase, it is our district’s intention to implement a total school reopening with multiple educational options. At the same time, we are prioritizing the well-being of our students by making significant efforts to comply with federal and state health and safety guidelines. In an effort to keep our students and parents informed, the district will be mailing a document that summarizes our Reopening Plan and other important information for our schools’ families in the near future. Thank you and have a good evening.

post_text:
Attention Middle School Students and Families,
On June 8th, Meyersdale Area Middle School Families are welcome to come to the middle school to receive student report cards and return text books, library books, and chromebooks if necessary. If students have not received their personal items from their school lockers, they will receive them on this evening. Sixth and seventh grade students should arrive between three and five p.m. Eighth grade students should arrive between six and seven p.m. At this time, eighth graders will be recognized with an Eighth Grade Promotion Drive Thru in which every student will receive a Promotion Packet of materials as a keepsake. Appointments can be made with the Middle School Office if June 8th is not a convenient date to receive or return items. Report cards will be mailed to all students who are not present on the evening of June 8th. Our faculty and staff are looking forward to seeing you. Thank you and have a good evening.

YEARBOOK DISTRIBUTION INFORMATION

- Yearbooks (grades 6 - 12) will be distributed on Tuesday, May 12th
- All students who pre-ordered and paid for a yearbook have been notified via email.
- Drive to the high school office
- Please only one person at a time at the high school doors
- A mask must be worn
- Prepaid orders with last names A - L from 8:30 - 9:30 AM
- Prepaid order with last names M - Z from 9:30 - 10:30 AM
- Extra yearbooks will go on sale at 10:30 AM until 11:15 AM
- Cost is $65 per book
- Cash and exact change only - change will NOT be available
- First come first serve - books will not be held!!
- Guidelines listed above must be followed
Email ccuster@masd.net with any questions

post_text:
**update**
Pick up time is from 11:30am-12:00pm at each location and will start tomorrow, March 17, 2020.

The Meyersdale Area School District is committed to the health and well-being of our students. During the weeks moving forward, we recognize the added responsibility placed upon families in the wake of school closures. For that reason, we are preparing to provide pickup meals for students. The service would provide breakfast and lunch items for all Meyersdale Area students.

In an effort to better prepare for distribution, we are asking you to indicate which pickup location would best suit your needs. The locations for pick up are:
- Meyersdale Area School District,
- Meyersdale Fire Department Parking Lot,
- Garrett Fire Department Parking Lot or
- Wellersburg Fire Department Parking Lot

Please respond to the one call now phone call, text message, or email so that we can ensure the correct number of meals. This is a survey only. More information will be given in a follow up message.

Thank you.

Meyersdale Area School District is currently accepting applications for substitute custodians.
All employees must obtain proper clearances and pass a physical and drug screening prior to employment. Candidates do not need these to interview.
To apply, please call for an application at 814-634-5123 ext. 306 or stop by and pick one up at the school administration office during school hours.
